<TEXT>
here are some facts about the seabrook 
nuclear plant 
project announced after shelving an earlier proposal in 1969 
public service company of new hampshire announced feb 1 1972 
that it planned to build two nuclear reactors at seabrook the 
first to start operating commercially in 1979 the second in 1981 
the utility initially estimated the entire project would cost less 
than 1 billion 
location on land surrounded by marshes less than two miles from 
hampton beach little more than two miles north of massachusetts 
and about 40 miles north of boston 
construction began july 7 1976 
construction completed unit 1 july 31 1986 at cost of more 
than 43 billion unit 2 canceled 1986 25 percent complete 
nuclear fuel loaded october 1986 
cost to date 65 billion as of thursday postcompletion costs 
have been for financing and operations 
design pressurizedwater reactor 
manufacturers reactor and steam supply system westinghouse 
generator general electric 
output 1150 megawatts enough electricity for about 1 million 
homes 
work force during peak construction more than 8000 now 
1475 including some contract employees 
demonstrations began before groundbreaking in 1976 peaked in 
late 1970s continue to present overall there have been more than 
3200 arrests in antiseabrook protests 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

