utilities from building nuclear plants carr said the other was 
public utility regulators refusal to allow construction costs to 
be passed on to ratepayers until a plant was finished 
such a ruling in new hampshire led public service company of new 
hampshire owner of the largest seabrook share to abandon one of 
two reactors in 1986 and declare bankruptcy in 1988 
