i think when people went to the polls they voted with their 
stomachs and i think they thought about the empty stomachs of 
their children said paul reichler a washington lawyer who 
advises president daniel ortega 
sundays vote for change from a fractured economy and the strain 
of civil war against the ussupported contras swept ortegas 
leftist sandinistas from power in favor of mrs chamorro who takes 
office april 25 it marks the end of sandinista government which 
began with the ouster of dictator anastasio somoza in 1979 
but while the example of eastern europe did not reach the 
average voter the forces that caused change there affected the 
atmosphere and structure of the campaign as well as the 
sandinistas decision to hold and accept the consequences of a free 
vote 
they had to change because the world was changing said 
mauricio diaz secretarygeneral of the social christian party 
the bush administration credits the soviet union and president 
mikhail s gorbachev with encouraging nicaraguas move to democracy 
additionally reductions in east bloc aid and the visible 
failures of socialism affected the sandinistas own economic and 
political policies 
the sandinistas started out trying to build a nation on the 
cuban model but they really gave up on that by 1984 diaz said 
he and other analysts say the sandinistas were driven to 
democracy and a mixedeconomy theory by the hostility of the united 
states and the horrible state of their own economy 
the process was gradual both impeded and propelled by the war 
against ussupported contra guerrillas impeded by the need to 
maintain wartime political discipline propelled by the damage the 
war did to the economy 
real change did not take place until the united states halted 
lethal aid to the contras in early 1988 
shortly after the us congress voted to cut off aid the 
sandinistas put in place an economic austerity plan an imf 
international monetary fund plan without the imf as ortega put 
it 
while some of the plans more draconian proposals for firing 
public employees were not carried out enough was done to hurt poor 
people badly according to patricia okane a researcher at the 
regional coordinator for economic and social research in managua 
the sandinistas began wooing the private sector and acknowledged 
errors in some of their confiscation and expropriation policies 
it was tropical perestroika they tried to reform the 
revolution but it was too late diaz said 
still there were noticeable changes in the last year private 
advertising in newspapers and on radio and television picked up 
new cars began to appear on the streets also new streetlights and 
some street repairs were made 
in a strange conjunction that also occurred in poland under 
wojciech jaruzelskis government the country held its first beauty 
pageant in years 
theyre very pragmatic i think they began those moves as pure 
tactics the opening towards democracy a mixed economy 
nonalignment but somehow it became more than tactics said diaz 
they took a big gamble and they really thought they were going 
to win they totally underestimated the effects of the economic 
crisis okane said 
ortega and other sandinistas insist their party is not anything 
like the communist parties of eastern europe 
ortega has said the comparison is invalid because he won 40 
percent of the vote much more than any communist party in eastern 
europe is likely to gain 
diaz noted that nicaragua was never ruled by an allencompassing 
single party 
there were always independent unions though weak there was 
always a private sector there was always a political opposition 
he said 
he believes the influence of a nearby and very interested united 
states was a factor 
people were tired of always fighting the united states he 
said now everyones waiting for the first mcdonalds to open 
the sandinistas are not complete democrats however said diaz 
they linked the party the army and security forces and the 
government in a kind of triangle he said 
theyve lost the government but they are currently fighting in 
negotations with the opposition to hold on to the partyarmy link 
their last hold on power 
diaz said he thought there was real irony in the sandinista 
evolution 
just as they were becoming democratic they lost an 
election he said 
