<TEXT>
former federal judge arlin m adams was 
appointed today to investigate allegations that former housing 
secretary samuel r pierce jr and top aides illegally steered 
government rent subsidies to politically connected developers 
adams was appointed an independent counsel by a special court to 
investigate allegations that pierce and top aides at the department 
of housing and urban development conspired to defraud the moderate 
rehabilitation program 
adams who served 17 years as a member of the 3rd us circuit 
court of appeals in philadelphia is now a private lawyer in that 
city and chairman of the board of directors of the university of 
pennsylvania law school 
the appointment had been sought by attorney general dick 
thornburgh following a 90day preliminary inquiry into the 
allegations by the justice departments public integrity section 
were glad that an independent counsel has been finally 
appointed and the investigation can proceed said robert plotkin 
a lawyer for pierce we have every reason to expect that judge 
adams will conduct the investigation in a fair and impartial 
manner 
adams 68 has been affiliated with the philadelphia law firm of 
schnader harrison segal and lewis since retiring from the court 
in 1986 
a former state secretary of public welfare he also chaired the 
pennsylvania trade association commission from 1967 to 1971 
in 1988 adams was approached by justice department officials 
about the possibility of becoming deputy attorney general in the 
waning days of the tenure of attorney general edwin meese iii 
adams said he had other professional commitments and was could not 
consider taking the post 
asked about what preparation he has had for his new appointment 
adams recalled in an interview today that as state welfare 
secretary in the 1960s i got involved in looking into alleged 
misuse of various government programs 
in a statement the special division of the us circuit court 
of appeals here said that adams brings to this investigation the 
judgment experience and ability acquired by many years of service 
as a federal circuit judge as a private practitioner and as a 
recognized leader of the courts and the bar of the nation 
under the jurisdiction set by the court adams is empowered to 
determine whether pierce and other department officials may have 
committed the crime of conspiracy to defraud the united states or 
any other federal crimes relating to the administration of the 
selection process of the departments moderate rehabilitation 
program from 1984 through 1988 
the special courts order also empowers adams to investigate any 
allegations of perjury obstruction of justice and destruction of 
evidence and intimidation of witnesses during the course of the 
investigation 
under the moderate rehabilitation program developers receive 
tax credits and rent subsidies for performing a moderate amount of 
rehabilitation on housing for lowincome citizens 
in his feb 1 application to the court for appointment of an 
independent counsel thornburgh cited reports of a widespread 
perception among developers and municipal officials that funds 
were being disbursed in disproportionate amounts to projects backed 
by prominent republicans acting as consultants or by former hud 
officials 
the justice departments preliminary inquiry included a review 
of voluminous reports compiled by huds inspector general as well 
as testimony before a house government operations subcommittee that 
held hearings on the agency last year 
the original request for an independent counsel was made by 
democratic members of the house judiciary committee they cited 
allegations of political favoritism as well as charges that pierce 
had lied under oath during congressional testimony last spring 
thornburgh found there was no basis for further allegations that 
pierce lied under oath 
pierce refused to answer further questions when called back 
twice to give additional testiony before the subcommittee he 
invoked his fifth amendment privilege against selfincrimination 
under the special prosecutor law the threejudge panel chaired 
by senior circuit judge george mackinnon is required to appoint an 
independent counsel after receiving a request to do so from the 
attorney general 
