about 50 south american 
indians who converted to judaism celebrated their first sabbath in 
this west bank settlement friday after immigrating from peru 
the tribes move to the occupied lands comes at a time of 
growing us pressure on israel to stop building or expanding 
jewish settlements in the west bank and gaza strip and demands 
that israel not settle soviet jews in those areas 
the indians who call themselves the sons of moses became 
interested in judaism 40 years ago while living near the town of 
cajamarca in northern peru said israeli rabbi eliahu aviahil 
two tribal elders began studying the old testament at the time 
and about 20 years later the whole tribe abandoned christianity and 
began living a jewish lifestyle the rabbi said on israel radio 
aviahil said he learned of the indians three years ago and 
initiated their formal conversion and immigration 
the tribes men underwent ritual circumcision before everyone in 
the group was converted six months ago by a special rabbinical 
court according to orthodox jewish law 
aviahil heads amishav a society that researches judaisms 10 
lost tribes which according to legend disappeared after the exile 
