our main priority is to convince the people that we do not 
wish a return to the old days not to win the elections said 
mohorita who became first secretary after the partys hardline 
leadership was ousted during last years democratic revolution 
a return to the thesis of oneparty rule must not be allowed 
this monopoly on power must be prevented he added 
after 41 years of orthodox oneparty communist rule 
czechoslovakia underwent a peaceful revolution last november and 
december that introduced political pluralism 
mohorita said the communists should not be concerned about 
winning the elections but rather must convince czechoslovaks that 
they now support democracy 
we have to show the people that we have been participating in 
these democratization processes from the beginning and if we 
have to be in opposition it will be a constructive one he said 
despite losing its hold on power the communist party still has 
some 1 million members or maybe a little less mohorita said 
the party claimed 17 million members before the start of last 
years revolution some 13 million of those people joined the 
party after the purge of half a million members that followed the 
1968 sovietled invasion that crushed the prague spring reform 
movement 
mohorita indicated that party members who do not support the new 
prodemocracy policy would be dropped from the ranks 
he admitted that an unspecified number of party members still 
favor orthodox oneparty rule but stressed that we have to part 
with these people 
mohorita said there was a need for deep critical but very 
serious analysis of the past four decades of communist rule but 
he complained of what he called increasingly sharp attacks against 
the party in the media it once controlled 
a career communist official mohorita led the statecontrolled 
socialist youth union until tumultuous changes in the party 
propelled him into the position of first secretary in december at 
the same time ladislav adamec was named chairman of the party 
