issued by the space agencys public affairs office nasa is 
pleased that after careful consideration the nrc panel found the 
material developed in nasas 90day study accurate and appropriate 
to the human exploration initiative at this stage in its 
development 
david beckwith the vice presidents press secretary said 
its a very interesting report and we are pleased and grateful 
the council said costs of the program are uncertain and 
likely to remain so for some time 
it said it appeared unlikely for technical and cost reasons 
that the space station could be built in time so that americans 
could reach mars by 2011 as envisioned in the most ambitious nasa 
plan the other nasa option calls for exploration in 2018 
the panel disagreed with the contention of scientists at the 
lawrence livermore national laboratory that humans could be placed 
on mars by the year 2000 it said that underestimates the many 
practical and difficult engineering and operational challenges 
involved 
