measuring 55 on the richter scale caused at least 127 million 
damage in the cities of claremont pomona la verne chino 
ontario rancho cucamonga montclair and upland and the counties of 
los angeles riverside and san bernardino 
the figure is very preliminary based on information provided 
by cities and counties said guerin 
the quake felt along the coast from san diego to santa barbara 
and as far east as las vegas was centered on an unnamed fault 
three miles northwest of this city 40 miles east of los angeles it 
toppled scores of chimneys shattered hundreds of windows and 
collapsed one buildings wall but remarkably caused no major 
injuries or deaths 
dozens of smaller aftershocks have rattled the area since 
there was no official estimate of the number of injured other 
than several dozen from the oes the most serious injuries 
officials said were a few broken bones 
only one person a pomona man was known to have been left 
homeless by the quake 
but the temblor spurred renewed calls for southern californians 
to prepare for the socalled big one a catastrophic earthquake 
measuring between 75 and 8 on the richter scale of ground motion 
a 1988 us geological survey report said that a quake that size is 
at least 60 percent likely by the year 2018 on the southern san 
andreas fault 
this is the handwriting on the wall and we better start 
