will be targeting people under two sections of federal law that 
call for mandatory sentencing 
one says anyone convicted of a felony crime of violence or drug 
charge who is carrying a gun automatically is sentenced for at 
least five years on the weaponpossession charge 
the other section says that a person who has three previous 
felony convictions for a violent crime or drug offense will be 
sentenced to at least 15 years on the firearm charge 
the task forces are being launched at the same time that atf 
faces cutbacks under the bush administrations proposed 1991 budget 
of 185 positions created by the 1990 anticrime initiative 
the cutbacks will be required because of the need to offset 
administratively uncontrolled overtime pay and inflation according 
to deconcinis spokesman who spoke on the condition of anonymity 
to cope with the additional expenses the atf is proposing to 
reduce firearmslaw enforcement personnel not specifically 
connected to drug cases by 122 people next year according to 
congressional documents 
