the impossibility doctrine was misplaced 
the issue is not whether it was possible for the vessel to 
come free but whether captain hazelwoods mistakes in not 
realizing the vessel was firmly aground and not recognizing the 
danger in refloating were reasonable the document said 
it argued that hazelwood made a mistake in thinking he could 
remove the impaled tanker from bligh reef 
