<TEXT>
the savannah river nuclear weapons plant in 
south carolina is inadequately protected against severe earthquakes 
and wont be fully protected for several years federal auditors 
said friday 
the report by the general accounting office the investigative 
arm of congress said the vulnerability to earthquake damage at 
savannah river has been known for many years but it said the 
government only recently made serious corrective efforts 
the plant situated along the savannah river near aiken has 
nuclear reactors to produce tritium a radioactive gas needed to 
make nuclear warheads the installation also contains other 
nuclearrelated buildings including a fuel processing center for 
the navy and a radioactive waste treatment building 
the three reactors have been closed for nearly two years because 
of safety problems one of the three is expected to resume 
production by the end of this year 
the auditors in a report requested by rep mike synar dokla 
chairman of the house government operations subcommittee on the 
environment and energy said seismic improvements at savannah river 
would not be completed for several years 
planning of improvements is under way but it will take 
several years to accomplish adequate seismic protection at savannah 
river the report said 
numerous systems and structures in the reactors and other 
nuclear facilities may not withstand the worst earthquake 
reasonably expected at the site and in the event of such an 
earthquake could threaten employees and the public with releases 
of radiation the report said 
catherine kaliniak an energy department spokeswoman said the 
department had not seen the report and would not comment until it 
had reviewed the conclusions 
the earthquake potential at savannah river is based mainly on 
the fact that a large earthquake estimated to have been the 
equivalent of about 7 on the richter scale occurred in south 
carolina in 1886 it was centered about 80 miles from where the 
weapons plant now stands and it caused extensive damage and loss 
of life 
the san francisco earthquake last october was measured at about 
71 on the richter scale 
each whole number increase on the richter scale means an ground 
motion increase by a factor of 10 
</TEXT>
