an accident occurred but for now theyre willing to wait and see 
diehard opponents said however they would not willing to 
concede defeat despite the nrcs decision massachusetts attorney 
general james shannon has promised to take the activists case to 
the courts 
its begun to wear people down life has to go on you cant 
just keep picketing said marie capello a seabrook resident 
but she said she would probably end up doing just that 
weve been trying to buck something so big and so powerful 
not only the plant itself but all the mucketymucks who run it 
she said but i dont see how i can stop doing any little thing 
until the bitter end 
