the justice department filed a 
sexdiscrimination lawsuit thursday to try to force the allmale 
virginia military institute to admit women 
federal authorities filed the lawsuit on behalf of an 
unidentified female high school student from northern virginia who 
complained last spring that she had been prohibited from attending 
the 150yearold statesupported school in nearby lexington 
the lawsuit argues that the schools maleonly admission policy 
violates the civil rights act and the 14th amendment it urges the 
us district court in roanoke to order the state of virginia and 
the school to remedy fully their discriminatory policies and 
practices 
the justice department also is reviewing complaints from two 
women who want to attend the citadel in charleston sc the 
nations only other public military college that admits males only 
among those named in the lawsuit were virginia gov l douglas 
wilder and the state council of higher education along with the 
institutes superintendent john w knapp and board of visitors 
president joseph m spivey 
the justice department wrote wilder and knapp last march warning 
them they would face a lawsuit if they did not agree by feb 20 to 
begin admitting women 
but state attorney general mary sue terry and the schools 
private fundraising organization came back with two lawsuits 
asking the federal court in roanoke to declare the colleges 
admission policy constitutional 
the justice department also filed motions thursday asking the 
court to dismiss the lawsuits filed by the state and the foundation 
spokesman tom joynes said school officials would have no comment 
on the federal governments action the governors and state 
attorney generals offices both declined to comment 
the lawsuit said the institute is a public body and the 
defendants have engaged in discrimination on the basis of sex by 
refusing to consider qualified females for admission to the 
fouryear undergraduate degree program 
the institute received 11 million in state aid this year 
almost half of its 25 million budget 
