an earthquake rattled communities northeast of 
tokyo early saturday the central meteorological agency said 
local police said no casualties or damage were reported 
the quake occurred at 1222 am and the agency located its 
epicenter at 32 miles beneath the earths surface in southwestern 
ibaraki state about 38 miles northeast of tokyo 
the temblor had a preliminary reading of 45 on the richter 
scale 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by ground motion recorded on a seismograph 
a quake that measures 4 can cause moderate damage and one which 
measures 5 can cause considerable damage 
