which was supporting the popular uprising against ceausescu brucan 
said the dictator was overthrown dec 22 and executed dec 25 
i was afraid he might use his attributes to deceive to take 
in the generals said brucan 74 
so we decided to test him asking him to make a public 
statement on the radio and tv and the key sentence of the 
statement was and i wrote it with my hands an explicit order to 
his troops and snipers to cease fire and surrender themselves 
vlad did not include that sentence in the statement he read and 
at a meeting of the war council that night brucan demanded to know 
why 
gen vlad showed once more his slippery manner brucan said 
he insisted that his statement was a categorical commitment to 
the revolution and that this was much more important because it 
gave a new political orientation to his troops 
when brucan persisted vlad got very irritated angry and 
said it was the first time that someone questioned his loyalty to 
