dan webb the irancontra prosecutor handling 
the case against john poindexter is described by colleagues as one 
of the finest trial attorneys in the country 
when he was us attorney in chicago he won convictions against 
crooked cops and corrupt judges 
webbs trademark as former president reagan found out two weeks 
ago is his skillful crossexamination of witnesses 
in videotaped testimony for poindexters trial reagan suggested 
it might have been all right to destroy documents in the 
irancontra affair webb countered by pulling out a written answer 
reagan had given two years ago to a federal grand jury saying that 
no destruction of documents had been authorized by the president 
when one of reagans answers strayed far afield from the 
prosecutors question webb angered the former chief executive by 
interrupting him to announce he had been unresponsive 
if they wanted to find one of the best trial lawyers in 
america they did republican gov james thompson of illinois 
who has known webb for 19 years said of last summers decision by 
irancontra prosecutors to hire webb for the poindexter case 
webb 44 is a partner at the chicago law firm of winston amp 
strawn 
he grew up in bushnell ill and applied to become an assistant 
us attorney in chicago in 1971 an interviewer wrote the letters 
nbbr on his application which stood for nice boy but rural 
recalls thenus attorney william bauer who hired him immediately 
webb was highly motivated sincere and he desperately wanted 
to be an assistant us attorney the combination made it so you 
couldnt turn him down recalls bauer now chief judge of the 7th 
us circuit court of appeals in chicago 
while running the us attorneys office in chicago webb 
personally tried the marquette 10 case ten chicago police 
officers were accused of taking bribes from drug dealers to protect 
drug activity and all 10 were convicted 
i think that had not dan webb gotten involved we would have 
