<TEXT>
concerted central bank intervention helped 
moderate the dollars rise on friday following the currencys 
recent foreign exchange surge that analysts credit to economic and 
political turmoil in other nations 
some of the sharpest gains have come against the currencies of 
west germany and japan both of which are undergoing times of 
economic uncertainty 
the dollar closed at 17200 west german marks friday in europe 
up sharply from the 16545 marks of feb 7 
against the japanese currency the dollar closed at 15028 
japanese yen friday in london inciting a round of dollar selling 
by the central banks of several countries including the federal 
reserve on feb 19 the dollar was quoted at 14452 yen 
its not so much that the dollar is going up but other 
