the deutschemark has dominated foreign exchange trading since 
the barriers between the two germanys began falling on nov 9 the 
dollar closed at 18475 marks that day but the west german 
currency shot higher on speculation that the countrys economy 
would boom as a result of the political changes in eastern europe 
but some of the euphoria has begun to wear off and is being 
replaced by the jitters the outcome of this months east german 
elections is unclear and there is concern that the planned 
unification of the east german and west german currencies may lead 
to an oversupply of marks increasing the danger of runaway 
inflation 
all the uncertainty has increased the risk of holding 
deutschemark assets logan said 
investors have begun selling some of their marks to preserve 
their profits and the dollar has advanced as a result 
the dollars close of 17200 marks in europe compared with 
thursdays level of 17145 in new york the dollar fell to 17150 
west german marks from 17194 thursday 
