cigna corp said friday it was dropping 
personal auto insurance coverage because the division generates 
little business and is only marginally profitable 
cignas specialty is commercial insurance coverage and is rated 
one of the nations largest in that area cigna has only 08 
percent of the national business in personal auto insurance 
the insurance giant had annual premiums of 115 billion last 
year of which personal auto insurance accounted for only 215 
million 
the personal auto insurance is only marginally profitable at 
best and therefore we have decided to stop cigna spokesman jim 
beattie said 
beattie said the problem stems from higher repair bills medical 
bills and legal expenses cigna does not generate enough business 
to offset those costs and could not in the near future he said 
cigna has decided to concentrate on its commercial coverage 
lines as well as continue restructuring its agency division the 
company sells to individuals and small businesses through 
independent agents cigna said it would be severing exclusive 
contracts with 220 independents by the end of next year 
two weeks ago the head of the division handling the 
independents david j prentiss resigned 
beattie said the company will generally quit writing new auto 
policies and agents will be asked to renew existing policies with 
other carriers as the policies come due 
because of the change beattie said socalled umbrella 
policies cigna has offered for complete insurance coverage through 
one company would not be renewed 
but he said the company will continue to write homeowner 
insurance even though it is also a very small part of cignas 
business commercial vehicle coverage also will continue to be 
available 
beattie said some personal auto insurance policies will be 
honored and sold by agents who hold exclusive contracts with cigna 
we will meet or exceed all state regulations and honor all 
contractual agreements he said 
cigna said no layoffs are expected because of the personal auto 
coverage decision 
